attributes/session.description: Gameplay attributes associated with a session

list.name: ServerControlsSetup
list.description: Does the server control the game's setup? If yes, the host's lobby settings will be disabled. Set automatically from the server's settings, can't be modified by HTTP or Lua APIs.

list.name: ServerControlsTrack
list.description: Does the server control the track selection? If yes, everyone's track selection will be disabled.

list.name: ServerControlsVehicleClass
list.description: Does the server control the vehicle class selection? If yes, everyone's vehicle selection will be restricted to vehicles from class VehicleClassId, any attempts to change to another class via the garage will not work. Should be always combined with the FORCE_SAME_VEHICLE_CLASS session flag.

list.name: ServerControlsVehicle
list.description: Does the server control the vehicle selection? If yes, everyone's vehicle selection will be restricted to vehicle VehicleModelId. Should be always combined with the FORCE_IDENTICAL_VEHICLE session flag.

list.name: GridSize
list.description: Total maximum grid size, including AI participants. Can be modified only for the 'next session' and can never be larger than the maximum session size set in the server config.

list.name: MaxPlayers
list.description: Maximum number of players. Can't be higher than GridSize, but can be lower and then the extra slots will be reserved for AI vehicles. Can be modified only for the 'next session'.

list.name: Practice1Length
list.description: Length of first practice session in minutes.

list.name: Practice2Length
list.description: Length of second practice session in minutes.

list.name: QualifyLength
list.description: Length of qualification session in minutes.

list.name: WarmupLength
list.description: Length of warmup session in minutes.

list.name: Race1Length
list.description: Race 1 length in lap count.

list.name: Race2Length
list.description: Race 2 length in lap count. Currently not used in multiplayer.

list.name: Flags
list.description: Session setup flags. The flag values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/flags/session or in Lua global tables lists.flags.session, SessionFlags and value_to_session_flag.

list.name: Privacy
list.description: Session privacy, defined when the session is created. Usually server-hosted sessions will be public and use password-protection or blacklists/whitelists to control who can join them. The possible values are 0 to 2, with 0 meaning public, 1 for friends only and 2 for private.

list.name: DamageType
list.description: Damage type. The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/damage or in Lua global tables lists.enums.damage, Damage and value_to_damage.

list.name: TireWearType
list.description: Tire wear type. The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/tire_wear or in Lua global tables lists.enums.tire_wear, TireWear and value_to_tire_wear.

list.name: FuelUsageType
list.description: Fuel usage type. The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/fuel_usage or in Lua global tables lists.enums.fuel_usage, FuelUsage and value_to_fuel_usage.

list.name: PenaltiesType
list.description: Penalties type. The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/penalties or in Lua global tables lists.enums.penalties, Penalties and value_to_penalties.

list.name: AllowedViews
list.description: Allowed cameras. Only Any (0) and CockpitHelmet (2) are supported by the game, writes of other values will be ignored. The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/allowed_view or in Lua global tables lists.enums.allowed_view, AllowedView and value_to_allowed_view.

list.name: TrackId
list.description: Track id. Players will be able to change this unless ServerControlsTrack is set to non-zero. The list of all valid tracks is available also via HTTP API at /api/list/tracks or in Lua global tables lists.tracks, id_to_track and name_to_track.

list.name: VehicleClassId
list.description: Vehicle class id, used when forcing vehicle class (session flag FORCE_SAME_VEHICLE_CLASS is set). If controlled from the server also set attribute ServerControlsVehicleClass. Latest class list is available also via HTTP API at /api/list/vehicle_classes and in Lua global tables lists.vehicle_classes, id_to_vehicle_class and name_to_vehicle_class.

list.name: VehicleModelId
list.description: Vehicle model id, used when forcing identical vehicles (session flag FORCE_IDENTICAL_VEHICLES is set). If controlled from the server also set attribute ServerControlsVehicle. Latest vehicle list is available also via HTTP API at /api/list/vehicles and in Lua global tables lists.vehicles, id_to_vehicle and name_to_vehicle.

list.name: DateYear
list.description: Starting race date - year.

list.name: DateMonth
list.description: Starting race date - month.

list.name: DateDay
list.description: Starting race date - day of month.

list.name: DateHour
list.description: Starting race date - hour of day.

list.name: DateMinute
list.description: Starting race date - minutes.

list.name: DateProgression
list.description: Race date/time progression multiplier. Only some values between 1 and 60 are valid, the game might change the requested value to closest valid one.

list.name: ForecastProgression
list.description: Time-based forecast progression multiplier. Only some values between 1 and 30 are valid, the game might change the requested value to closest valid one.

list.name: WeatherSlots
list.description: Number of weather slots in use. Set to 0 to use real weather, and to a number between 1 and 4 to interpolate between predefined templates in WeatherSlotN.

list.name: WeatherSlot1
list.description: Fixed weather, slot 1. The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/weather or in Lua global tables lists.enums.weather, Weather and value_to_weather.

list.name: WeatherSlot2
list.description: Fixed weather, slot 2. The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/weather or in Lua global tables lists.enums.weather, Weather and value_to_weather.

list.name: WeatherSlot3
list.description: Fixed weather, slot 3. The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/weather or in Lua global tables lists.enums.weather, Weather and value_to_weather.

list.name: WeatherSlot4
list.description: Fixed weather, slot 4. See The enum values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/enums/weather or in Lua global tables lists.enums.weather, Weather and value_to_weather.

list.name: GameMode
list.description: Game mode hash. Multiplayer sessions always use -1958878043 or 'MP_RaceWeekend'.

list.name: Latitude
list.description: Track's latitude, in degrees multiplied by 1000 (so 180000 corresponds to 180 degrees).

list.name: Longitude
list.description: Track's longitude, in degrees multiplied by 1000.

list.name: Altitude
list.description: Track's base altitude, in millimeters.

list.name: SessionState
list.description: Multiplayer session state. Valid values are None, Lobby, Loading, Race, PostRace, Returning.

list.name: SessionStage
list.description: Multiplayer session flow/stage. Valid values are Practice1, Practice2, Qualifying, Warmup, FormationLap, Race1. Race2 might be used if two-race format is implemented in multiplayer.

list.name: SessionPhase
list.description: Race manager phase. This is relatively internal value used during race startup synchronization. Valid values are PreCountDownSync, PreRace, CountDownWait, CountDown, Green, Invalid.

list.name: SessionTimeElapsed
list.description: Time elapsed since the start of the session (this stage), in seconds. Note that this value might currently start counting during loading and otehr transitions, and then reset back to zero when the race really starts.

list.name: SessionTimeDuration
list.description: Time elapsed since the start of the session, in seconds.

list.name: NumParticipantsValid
list.description: Number of 'valid' race participants, or positions.

list.name: NumParticipantsDisqualified
list.description: Number of disqualified participants.

list.name: NumParticipantsRetired
list.description: Number of retired participants.

list.name: NumParticipantsDNF
list.description: Number of DNF participants.

list.name: NumParticipantsFinished
list.description: Number of finished participants.

list.name: CurrentYear
list.description: Current race date - year.

list.name: CurrentMonth
list.description: Current race date - month.

list.name: CurrentDay
list.description: Current race date - day of month.

list.name: CurrentHour
list.description: Current race date - hour of day.

list.name: CurrentMinute
list.description: Current race date - minutes.

list.name: RainDensity
list.description: Rain density, this implies how "visually" rainy the weather is. Values between 0 and 1000 are valid.

list.name: WetnessOnPath
list.description: Average wetness on path. Values between 0 and 1000 are valid.

list.name: WetnessOffPath
list.description: Average wetness off path. Values between 0 and 1000 are valid.

list.name: WetnessAverage
list.description: Overall average wetness on track. Values between 0 and 1000 are valid.

list.name: WetnessPredictedMax
list.description: Predicted maximum wetness on track, if available.

list.name: WetnessMaxLevel
list.description: Maximum water level, this implies how "physically" rainy the weather is. Values between 0 and 1000 are valid.

list.name: TemperatureAmbient
list.description: Ambient temperature, in deg Celsius multiplied by 1000 (so 37000 is 37 degrees Celsius).

list.name: TemperatureTrack
list.description: Track temperature, in deg Celsius multiplied by 1000.

list.name: AirPressure
list.description: Air pressure.

attributes/member.description: Gameplay attributes associated with a session's member (player)

list.name: VehicleId
list.description: Player's vehicle id. Latest vehicle list is available also via HTTP API at /api/list/vehicles and in Lua global tables lists.vehicles, id_to_vehicle and name_to_vehicle.

list.name: LiveryId
list.description: Livery id used on the player's vehicle. Latest vehicle+liveries list is available via HTTP API at /api/list/liveries and in Lua global tables lists.vehicles, id_to_vehicle and name_to_vehicle. It is not included in the Values and Types documentation.

list.name: LoadState
list.description: Player's loading state. This is an internal variable with many possible states. There are two sets of states, one for the admin (host) player and another for clients, the states range from ready-for-sync to syncing to loading to ready.

list.name: RaceStatFlags
list.description: Player's race stat flags. The flag values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/flags/player or in Lua global tables lists.flags.player, PlayerFlags and value_to_player_flag.

list.name: Ping
list.description: Player's ping to the dedicated server. This is the round trip time, so "there and back".

attributes/participant.description: Gameplay attributes associated with a session's participant (car)

list.name: RefId
list.description: RefId of the session member owning this participant.

list.name: Name
list.description: Participant's name. Same as the name of the owning player if this is a player participant, otherwise a generated AI name.

list.name: IsPlayer
list.description: 1 if this participant is controlled by the owning player, 0 if this is an AI participant.

list.name: GridPosition
list.description: Starting grid position of the participant.

list.name: VehicleId
list.description: Participant's vehicle id. Latest vehicle list is available also via HTTP API at /api/list/vehicles and in Lua global tables lists.vehicles, id_to_vehicle and name_to_vehicle.

list.name: LiveryId
list.description: Livery id used on the participant's vehicle. Latest vehicle+liveries list is available via HTTP API at /api/list/liveries and in Lua global tables lists.vehicles, id_to_vehicle and name_to_vehicle. It is not included in the Values and Types documentation.

list.name: RacePosition
list.description: Current race position of the participant.

list.name: CurrentLap
list.description: Current lap. Zero if not in a lap yet.

list.name: CurrentSector
list.description: Current sector's index (1 to 3 for valid circuit sectors). Sector time corresponding to this sector is the current sector time. Other sector times are the times last set inn those sectors, if available.

list.name: Sector1Time
list.description: Last time set in sector 1, or current sector 1 time if that sector is the CurrentSector, in milliseconds.

list.name: Sector2Time
list.description: Last time set in sector 2, or current sector 2 time if that sector is the CurrentSector, in milliseconds.

list.name: Sector3Time
list.description: Last time set in sector 3, or current sector 3 time if that sector is the CurrentSector, in milliseconds.

list.name: LastLapTime
list.description: Last lap time, in milliseconds.

list.name: FastestLapTime
list.description: Fastest lap time, in milliseconds.

list.name: State
list.description: Racing state of the participant. Valid values are Racing, Finished, DNF, Disqualified, Retired, InGarage, EnteringPits, InPits, ExitingPits.

list.name: HeadlightsOn
list.description: Flag set to non-zero if the participant's headlights are turned on.

list.name: WipersOn
list.description: Flag set to non-zero if the participant's wipers are turned on.

list.name: Speed
list.description: The participant's vehicle speed, in kph.

list.name: Gear
list.description: Current gear.

list.name: RPM
list.description: Current RPM.

list.name: PositionX
list.description: Position on map, X coordinate, in millimeters.

list.name: PositionY
list.description: Position on map, Y coordinate, in millimeters.

list.name: PositionZ
list.description: Position on map, Z coordinate, in millimeters.

list.name: Orientation
list.description: Vehicle orientation (heading) on the map, in degrees from 0 to 360.

events.description: All events that can be present in the log available at /api/log and /api/log/range

list.name: SessionSetup
list.description: This event is generated when the game starts loading. Is includes the basic information about the session's setup. More can be queried from the detailed setup attributes, they will no longer change after this event happens.

attributes.name: GridSize
attributes.description: Total maximum grid size, including AI participants. Can be modified only for the 'next session' and can never be larger than the maximum session size set in the server config.

attributes.name: MaxPlayers
attributes.description: Maximum number of players. Can't be higher than GridSize, but can be lower and then the extra slots will be reserved for AI vehicles. Can be modified only for the 'next session'.

attributes.name: Practice1Length
attributes.description: Length of first practice session in minutes.

attributes.name: Practice2Length
attributes.description: Length of second practice session in minutes.

attributes.name: QualifyLength
attributes.description: Length of qualification session in minutes.

attributes.name: WarmupLength
attributes.description: Length of warmup session in minutes.

attributes.name: Race1Length
attributes.description: Race 1 length in lap count.

attributes.name: Race2Length
attributes.description: Race 2 length in lap count. Currently not used in multiplayer.

attributes.name: Flags
attributes.description: Session setup flags. The flag values are available also via HTTP API at /api/list/flags/session or in Lua global tables lists.flags.session, SessionFlags and value_to_session_flag.

attributes.name: TrackId
attributes.description: Track id. Players will be able to change this unless ServerControlsTrack is set to non-zero. The list of all valid tracks is available also via HTTP API at /api/list/tracks or in Lua global tables lists.tracks, id_to_track and name_to_track.

attributes.name: GameMode
attributes.description: Game mode hash. Multiplayer sessions always use -1958878043 or 'MP_RaceWeekend'.

list.name: StateChanged
list.description: This event is generated whenever the multiplayer session's state changes.

attributes.name: PreviousState
attributes.description: Previous session state.

attributes.name: NewState
attributes.description: New session state. Valid values are None, Lobby, Loading, Race, PostRace, Returning.

list.name: StageChanged
list.description: This event is generated whenever the multiplayer session's stage (phase) changes.

attributes.name: PreviousStage
attributes.description: Previous session stage.

attributes.name: NewStage
attributes.description: New session stage. Valid values are Practice1, Practice2, Qualifying, Warmup, FormationLap, Race1, Race2.

attributes.name: Length
attributes.description: Length of the new stage. In minutes or laps, depending on the stage. Matches value sent in the setup event.

list.name: SessionCreated
list.description: This event is generated when someone joins an empty server and a new multiplayer session is created.

list.name: SessionDestroyed
list.description: This event is generated when all players leave the server and the multiplayer session is destroyed.

list.name: ServerChat
list.description: This event contains a chat message sent by the server.

attributes.name: RefId
attributes.description: RefId of the recipient of the message, or zero if this message is sent to all players.

attributes.name: Message
attributes.description: The message.

list.name: PlayerJoined
list.description: This event is generated when a new player joins the session. The player is not authenticated with Steam at this point and will not be reported to the game yet.

attributes.name: Name
attributes.description: Player's name.

attributes.name: SteamId
attributes.description: Player's Steam id.

list.name: Authenticated
list.description: This event is generated when Steam authenticates a player.

list.name: PlayerLeft
list.description: This event is generated when a player leaves the session.

attributes.name: Reason
attributes.description: Reason for the leave.

attributes.name: GameReasonId
attributes.description: If leaving via game call (on their own or kicked), the reason id used by the game. Otherwise this attribute won't be set at all. Usual game-specific values are: 1 when the user leaves via the UI, 2 when kicked, 3 or 5 when disconnected. But the value can't be always fully trusted.

list.name: PlayerChat
list.description: Event with a chat message sent by a player to everyone else in the session.

attributes.name: Message
attributes.description: The message.

list.name: ParticipantCreated
list.description: This event is generated when a new participant is created.

attributes.name: Name
attributes.description: Participant's name. Same as the player owning the participant if this is a player's vehicle, otherwise a generated AI name.

attributes.name: IsPlayer
attributes.description: 1 if this participant is controlled by the owning player, 0 if this is an AI participant.

attributes.name: VehicleId
attributes.description: Participant's vehicle id. Latest vehicle list is available also via HTTP API at /api/list/vehicles and in Lua global tables lists.vehicles, id_to_vehicle and name_to_vehicle.

attributes.name: LiveryId
attributes.description: Livery id used on the participant's vehicle. Latest vehicle+liveries list is available via HTTP API at /api/list/liveries and in Lua global tables lists.vehicles, id_to_vehicle and name_to_vehicle. It is not included in the Values and Types documentation.

list.name: ParticipantDestroyed
list.description: This event is generated when an existing participant is destroyed.

list.name: Sector
list.description: This event is generated when a participant crosses a sector boundary.

attributes.name: Lap
attributes.description: Lap number. When crossing the finish sector this is the finished lap's number, the lap counter is advanced after this event happens.

attributes.name: Sector
attributes.description: Index of the sector boundary crossed by the participant. 0=start, 1,2=sectors, 3=finish.

attributes.name: SectorTime
attributes.description: Final time set in the finished sector, in milliseconds.

attributes.name: TotalTime
attributes.description: Total race time, in milliseconds.

attributes.name: CountThisLap
attributes.description: One if this lap counts, zero if the lap is not considered valid.

attributes.name: CountThisLapTimes
attributes.description: One if this lap's time counts, zero if the time has been invalidated (usually by going off-track).

list.name: Lap
list.description: This event is generated whenever a participant finishes a lap.

attributes.name: Lap
attributes.description: Lap number of the finished lap.

attributes.name: LapTime
attributes.description: Lap time, in milliseconds.

attributes.name: Sector1Time
attributes.description: Sector 1 time, in milliseconds.

attributes.name: Sector2Time
attributes.description: Sector 2 time, in milliseconds.

attributes.name: Sector3Time
attributes.description: Sector 3 time, in milliseconds.

attributes.name: RacePosition
attributes.description: Race position.

attributes.name: DistanceTravelled
attributes.description: Distance travelled in this lap, in meters.

attributes.name: CountThisLapTimes
attributes.description: One if this lap's time counts, zero if the time has been invalidated (usually by going off-track).

list.name: State
list.description: This event is generated when a participant's state changes.

attributes.name: PreviousState
attributes.description: Previous state.

attributes.name: NewState
attributes.description: New state. Valid values are Racing, Finished, DNF, Disqualified, Retired, InGarage, EnteringPits, InPits, ExitingPits

list.name: Results
list.description: This event is generated just before the current stage finishes, and contains the results for this participant.

attributes.name: RacePosition
attributes.description: Participant's final race position. Relevant only in qualification and race stages.

attributes.name: Lap
attributes.description: Current lap number.

attributes.name: VehicleId
attributes.description: Id of vehicle used.

attributes.name: State
attributes.description: Participant's state. Valid values are Racing, Finished, DNF, Disqualified, Retired, InGarage, EnteringPits, InPits, ExitingPits.

attributes.name: TotalTime
attributes.description: Participant's total race time.

attributes.name: FastestLapTime
attributes.description: Participant's fastest lap time.

list.name: Impact
list.description: This event is generated when a participant collides with something. This event is reported by one of the participants in the collision, and can contain information about the other participant (unless this is a collision with the environment). Which participant reports this event is not defined, it is not the one who "caused" the collision. Because of the assymetric nature of physical collisions in multiplayer, the other participant might report the same event too, with slightly different values.

attributes.name: OtherParticipantId
attributes.description: Other participant's id, or -1 if not collided into a participant.

attributes.name: CollisionMagnitude
attributes.description: Magnitude of the impact. Value reported by physics multiplied by 1000, with 0 meaning no impact (never reported) and 1000 being the highest value.

list.name: CutTrackStart
list.description: This event is reported when a participant goes off-track.

attributes.name: Lap
attributes.description: Current lap.

attributes.name: RacePosition
attributes.description: Current race position.

attributes.name: IsMainBranch
attributes.description: Is this the main branch of the track?

attributes.name: LapTime
attributes.description: Current time into lap, in milliseconds.

list.name: CutTrackEnd
list.description: This event is reported when a participant returns back to track. This matches the previous CutTrackStart event reported for the participant.

attributes.name: ElapsedTime
attributes.description: Time elapsed while off-track.

attributes.name: SkippedTime
attributes.description: Estimated time skipped by cutting the track.

attributes.name: PlaceGain
attributes.description: Number of places gained or lost while off-track.

attributes.name: PenaltyValue
attributes.description: Penalty value computed from various cut-track variables.

attributes.name: PenaltyThreshold
attributes.description: Minimum penalty value for the cut to be considered for actual penalty.

enums/tire_wear.description: Enum describing various tier wear options

enums/fuel_usage.description: Enum describing various fuel usage options
